Modifications relative to upstream
----------------------------------

1. `programs/` — a port of `jito-tip-distribution` from `anchor-lang`
   `0.31.1` to `anchor-lang` `1.0.1` for use as the cf-invariants-jito
   harness target. Build-system and dependency surfaces were updated to
   the newer anchor-lang; program logic is preserved.

2. `references/jito_tipdist_ref/` — a clean baseline copy of the upstream
   `tip-distribution` program plus four Crucible fuzz fixtures
   (`fuzz/jito_claim_conservation`, `fuzz/jito_no_double_claim`,
   `fuzz/jito_merkle_authority`, `fuzz/jito_admin_gating`). The
   fuzz-fixture sources are CaliperForge-authored harness code, not
   upstream code.

3. `references/jito_tipdist_ref_planted_*/` — four CaliperForge-authored
   "planted-bug" variants of the clean reference. Each variant introduces
   a small, deliberate logic regression into the tip-distribution program
   source so the Crucible harness can prove the corresponding invariant
   class fires (planted >= 1 violation) while the clean reference holds
   (clean = 0 violations). The planted modifications are listed in
   `README.md` and visible as diffs against `references/jito_tipdist_ref/`.

